In this article, President Obama proclaims November 2016 as National Adoption Month in the United States. He highlights the importance of adoptive parents in providing stable and loving families for children in need. The President acknowledges that there are still many children waiting to be adopted from foster care and emphasizes the need to ensure every child can find their forever family. He mentions that his administration has taken steps to eliminate barriers to adoption by extending tax credits and providing financial incentives to child welfare agencies. President Obama also recognizes National Adoption Day, which takes place on the Saturday before Thanksgiving, and applauds the thousands of adoptions that are finalized on this day. He urges all Americans to observe National Adoption Month by finding permanent and caring families for children in need and supporting the families who care for them.